@ENDNODE

@NODE ApplicationAddWindow "RapaGUI Guide"

   @{b}NAME@{ub}
        Application.AddWindow -- add detached window object to application object

   @{b}SYNOPSIS@{ub}
        moai.DoMethod(id, "AddWindow", window)

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
        This method can be used to add a detached window object to the
        application object. Once the window object has been attached to the
        application object, you can open the window by setting its @{"Window.Open" LINK WindowOpen}
        attribute.

        Detached window objects can be created either by calling the
        @{"moai.CreateObject()" LINK moaiCreateObject} function or by explicitly detaching them from their
        parent by using the @{"Application.RemoveWindow" LINK ApplicationRemoveWindow} method.

        Please do note that you must not call Application.AddWindow for dialogs
        created using @{"moai.CreateDialog()" LINK moaiCreateDialog} since @{"moai.CreateDialog()" LINK moaiCreateDialog} already
        calls Application.AddWindow internally.

   @{b}INPUTS@{ub}
        id        id of the application object
        window    id of the window object to add

   @{b}EXAMPLE@{ub}
        see @{"moai.CreateObject()" LINK moaiCreateObject}

@ENDNODE

@NODE ApplicationContextMenu "RapaGUI Guide"

   @{b}NAME@{ub}
        Application.ContextMenu -- set context menu for application (V2.0)

   @{b}PLATFORMS@{ub}
        Windows, macOS, Linux

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
        If your application has installed an icon in the system tray by using
        Hollywood's "SetTrayIcon()" function, you can use this attribute to add
        a context menu to the application's tray icon. Just set this attribute
        to an identifier of a MOAI object derived from @{"Menu class" LINK Menu} and your
        application's icon in the system tray will get a context menu. Whenever
        the user presses the right mouse button on the icon in the system tray,
        the context menu will be shown.

        See @{"Context menus" LINK ContextMenus} for an example.

   @{b}TYPE@{ub}
        MOAI object

   @{b}APPLICABILITY@{ub}
        @{"I" LINK Applicability}

@ENDNODE

@NODE ApplicationHelpFile "MUI Royale Guide"

   @{b}NAME@{ub}
        Application.HelpFile -- set/get application help file (V2.0)

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
        Set a help file for the application. On Windows this should point to a
        CHM file, on Amiga to an AmigaGuide file and on all other platforms to a
        directory which contains all HTML files belonging to the application's
        manual (the main file must be called index.html, the index file must be
        called findex.html) help file.

        Once you have defined a help file, you can then use @{"Application.ShowHelp" LINK ApplicationShowHelp}
        and @{"Application.ShowHelpNode" LINK ApplicationShowHelpNode} to open the help file.

        This is currently unsupported on Android.

   @{b}TYPE@{ub}
        String

   @{b}APPLICABILITY@{ub}
        @{"ISG" LINK Applicability}

@ENDNODE

@NODE ApplicationIcon "MUI Royale Guide"

   @{b}NAME@{ub}
        Application.Icon -- set application icon

   @{b}PLATFORMS@{ub}
        AmigaOS and compatibles only

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
        This tag allows you to set the icon that will be shown on Workbench
