@NODE AreaFontSize "RapaGUI Guide"

   @{b}NAME@{ub}
        Area.FontSize -- set/get font size for object (V2.0)

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
        Set or get the font size for the object. The font size must be either a
        value in points (non-Amiga) or in pixels (Amiga) or one of the following
        predefined font sizes:

        Normal    Normal font size.

        Small     Small font size.

        Big       Big font size.

        Note that on AmigaOS and compatibles this can only be set at
        initialization time. You cannot change fonts for existing objects. Also,
        on AmigaOS you must also set @{"Area.FontName" LINK AreaFontName} if you set this attribute to
        a numeric size. If you pass one of the predefined font sizes (see above)
        on AmigaOS, you must not set @{"Area.FontName" LINK AreaFontName}, though.

        Also note that on AmigaOS Area.FontSize can't be used with widgets of
        type @{"Label class" LINK Label}. Use @{"Text class" LINK Text} class.

   @{b}TYPE@{ub}
        Number or string (see above for possible values)

   @{b}APPLICABILITY@{ub}
        @{"ISG" LINK Applicability}

