@NODE Busybar "RapaGUI Guide"
@{b}Overview@{ub}

    Busybar class derives from @{"Area class" LINK Area} and creates a widget which shows an
    animation indicating that the application is currently in a busy state. This
    animation, however, just shows activity but no progress. If you would like
    to visualize progress, use @{"Progressbar class" LINK Progressbar} instead. See @{"Progressbar class" LINK Progressbar}
    for details.

    Once you've created an object of Busybar class, you have to call
    @{"Busybar.Move" LINK BusybarMove} repeatedly to move the animation. This can be achieved by
    setting up an interval timer using Hollywood's "SetInterval()" function.

    @{"Busybar.Move                      " LINK BusybarMove} Draw next animation frame
    @{"Busybar.Reset                     " LINK BusybarReset} Stop animation
@ENDNODE

