@NODE Group "RapaGUI Guide"
@{b}Overview@{ub}

    Group class can be used to lay out a number of children in various ways.
    When the parent's size changes, groups relayout their children which can be
    very useful to create windows that are freely resizable in all directions.

    The following different group types are supported by RapaGUI:

    <hgroup>  Group children will be laid out in a row (vertical).

    <vgroup>  Group children will be laid out in a column (horizontal).

    <colgroup>
              Group children will be laid out in columns.

    <scrollgroup>
              A group with scrollbars. This is a special group which shows an
              embedded group with scrollbars. See @{"Scrollgroup class" LINK Scrollgroup} for details.

    Column groups are useful if you need to have identical widget sizes for all
    your children in a group for a more pleasant visual appearance. For example,
    imagine a form made up of text entry widgets and text objects. It is
    recommended to use a <colgroup> here because it leads to a clear and ordered
    visual appearance. Here's an example:

        <colgroup columns="2">
           <label>Name</label>
           <textentry/>
           <label>Street</label>
           <textentry/>
           <label>City</label>
           <textentry/>
           <label>Zip code</label>
           <textentry/>
           <label>Country</label>
           <textentry/>
           <label>Telephone</label>
           <textentry/>
           <label>Email</label>
           <textentry/>
        </colgroup>

    If we used a <vgroup> with one <hgroup> per row the appearance would be
    pretty bad because the text entry widget's width would be different for each
    line which looks pretty ugly.

    Note that Group class doesn't derive from @{"Area class" LINK Area} because groups do not
    exist as physical widgets but they are just layout tools for their child
    widgets or groups. This is why you cannot use attributes and methods from
    @{"Area class" LINK Area} on group objects.

    @{"Group.Append                      " LINK GroupAppend} Add detached object as last group child
    @{"Group.Color                       " LINK GroupColor} Set group background color
    @{"Group.Columns                     " LINK GroupColumns} Define group columns
    @{"Group.ExitChange                  " LINK GroupExitChange} Terminate group modification state
    @{"Group.Frame                       " LINK GroupFrame} Create framed group
    @{"Group.FrameTitle                  " LINK GroupFrameTitle} Set title for framed group
    @{"Group.HAlign                      " LINK GroupHAlign} Set default horizontal alignment
    @{"Group.Hide                        " LINK GroupHide} Show/hide group
    @{"Group.HorizSpacing                " LINK GroupHorizSpacing} Set horizontal spacing
    @{"Group.Icon                        " LINK GroupIcon} Set group icon
    @{"Group.IconScale                   " LINK GroupIconScale} Configure automatic image scaling
    @{"Group.IconType                    " LINK GroupIconType} Set icon type to use
    @{"Group.InitChange                  " LINK GroupInitChange} Prepare group addition or removal of children
    @{"Group.Insert                      " LINK GroupInsert} Insert detached object after specified child
    @{"Group.Padding                     " LINK GroupPadding} Set padding space between frame and children
    @{"Group.Paint                       " LINK GroupPaint} Request paint notification
    @{"Group.Prepend                     " LINK GroupPrepend} Add detached object as first group child
    @{"Group.Remove                      " LINK GroupRemove} Detach child from group
    @{"Group.SameSize                    " LINK GroupSameSize} Set same size for all children
