@NODE HSplitter "RapaGUI Guide"
@{b}Overview@{ub}

    HSplitter class is a special variant of @{"Group class" LINK Group}. It creates a
    horizontal group of two children with a sash between them that allows the
    user to individually adjust the sizes of the group's two children by
    dragging the sash.

    Note that HSplitter groups must always contain exactly two children.
    Additionally, the children must also be sizable because HSplitter class
    allows its children to be resized. Here is an example XML excerpt for
    creating a horizontal splitter layout with two textviews:

        <hsplitter>
            <textview>One</textview>
            <textview>Two</textview>
        </hsplitter>

    HSplitter class is available since RapaGUI 2.0.

    @{"HSplitter.Border                 " LINK HSplitterBorder} Set sash border style
    @{"HSplitter.Gravity                " LINK HSplitterGravity} Set/get sash gravity
    @{"HSplitter.MinPaneSize            " LINK HSplitterMinPaneSize} Set/get minimum pane size
    @{"HSplitter.Position               " LINK HSplitterPosition} Set/get sash position
    @{"HSplitter.Split                  " LINK HSplitterSplit} Split the panes
    @{"HSplitter.Unsplit                " LINK HSplitterUnsplit} Unsplit the panes
@ENDNODE

@NODE HSplitterBorder "RapaGUI Guide"

   @{b}NAME@{ub}
        HSplitter.Border -- set sash border style (V2.0)

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
        Set this to FALSE to make the sash use a different border style. Note
        that this is not supported on all platforms.

   @{b}TYPE@{ub}
        Boolean

   @{b}APPLICABILITY@{ub}
        @{"I" LINK Applicability}

@ENDNODE

@NODE HSplitterGravity "RapaGUI Guide"

   @{b}NAME@{ub}
        HSplitter.Gravity -- set/get sash gravity (V2.0)

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
        Set or get the sash gravity. Gravity is a value between 0 and 100 which
        controls the position of the sash while resizing the splitter group. The
        gravity value tells splitter group how much the left child will grow
        while resizing. For example:

        - 0: Only the right child is automatically resized.
        - 50: Both children grow by equal size.
        - 100: Only the left child grows.

        The default sash gravity is 0.

   @{b}TYPE@{ub}
        Number

   @{b}APPLICABILITY@{ub}
        @{"SG" LINK Applicability}

@ENDNODE

@NODE HSplitterMinPaneSize "RapaGUI Guide"

   @{b}NAME@{ub}
        HSplitter.MinPaneSize -- set/get minimum pane size (V2.0)

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
        Set or get the minimum pane size. The default minimum pane size is 0,
        which means that either pane can be reduced to zero by dragging the
        sash, thus removing one of the panes. To prevent this behaviour (and
        veto out-of-range sash dragging), set a minimum size, for example 20.

        This value is in @{"device-independent pixels" LINK DIP}.

   @{b}TYPE@{ub}
        Number

   @{b}APPLICABILITY@{ub}
        @{"ISG" LINK Applicability}

@ENDNODE

@NODE HSplitterPosition "RapaGUI Guide"

   @{b}NAME@{ub}
        HSplitter.Position -- set/get sash position (V2.0)

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
        Set or get the position of the sash dividing the group's children. This
        value is in @{"device-independent pixels" LINK DIP}.

   @{b}TYPE@{ub}
        Number

   @{b}APPLICABILITY@{ub}
        @{"SG" LINK Applicability}

@ENDNODE

@NODE HSplitterSplit "RapaGUI Guide"

   @{b}NAME@{ub}
        HSplitter.Split -- split the panes (V2.0)

   @{b}SYNOPSIS@{ub}
        moai.DoMethod(id, "Split", pos)

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
        This splits the group into two panes. The "pos" argument specifies the
        position of the sash in @{"device-independent pixels" LINK DIP}. If this value is
        positive, it specifies the size of the left pane. If it is negative, its
        absolute value gives the size of the right pane. Finally, specify 0 to
        choose the default position (half of the total window width).

   @{b}INPUTS@{ub}
        id        id of the splitter object
        pos       desired sash position

@ENDNODE

@NODE HSplitterUnsplit "RapaGUI Guide"

   @{b}NAME@{ub}
        HSplitter.Unsplit -- unsplit the panes (V2.0)

   @{b}SYNOPSIS@{ub}
        moai.DoMethod(id, "Unsplit", idx)

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
        This unsplits the panes and hides the pane specified in "idx". If "idx"
        is 0, the left pane will be hidden, if it is 1, the right pane will be
        hidden. To make both panes visible again, use the @{"HSplitter.Split" LINK HSplitterSplit}
        method.

   @{b}INPUTS@{ub}
        id        id of the splitter object
        idx       index of pane to remove

@ENDNODE

@NODE HTMLview "RapaGUI Guide"
@{b}Overview@{ub}

