@NODE Image "RapaGUI Guide"
@{b}Overview@{ub}

    Image class derives from @{"Area class" LINK Area} and shows the specified image. The image
    pixel data is taken from a Hollywood brush or icon, depending on what is set
    in @{"Image.BrushType" LINK ImageBrushType}.

    Here is an example XML declaration:

        <image brush="1"/>

    The XML code above creates an image object from Hollywood brush number 1.
    Image class fully supports mask and alpha channel transparency in Hollywood
    brushes/icons so you can also embed images with transparent areas.

    @{"Image.Brush                       " LINK ImageBrush} Set image to display
    @{"Image.BrushScale                  " LINK ImageBrushScale} Configure automatic image scaling
    @{"Image.BrushType                   " LINK ImageBrushType} Set image type to use
