@NODE ListviewCompareItems "RapaGUI Guide"

   @{b}NAME@{ub}
        Listview.CompareItems -- determine how entries should be sorted

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
        When setting up a notification on this attribute, RapaGUI will run your
        event callback whenever it needs to sort the list entries. The callback
        function will receive two entries as arguments and it has to determine
        which entry should be put first.

        Your event handler will be called with the following extra arguments:

        Entry1:   The first entry.

        Entry2:   The second entry.

        Your callback function then has to return a value that indicates how the
        two entries should be aligned in the listview. If entry 1 should be
        placed before 2, your callback has to return -1. If entry 1 should be
        placed after entry 2, your callback has to return 1. If the two entries
        are the same, return 0.

        See @{"Notifications" LINK Notifications} for details.

   @{b}TYPE@{ub}
        Boolean

   @{b}APPLICABILITY@{ub}
        @{"N" LINK Applicability}

@ENDNODE

