@NODE ListviewEdit "RapaGUI Guide"

   @{b}NAME@{ub}
        Listview.Edit -- prompt user to edit an item

   @{b}SYNOPSIS@{ub}
        moai.DoMethod(id, "Edit", row, column)

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
        This method can be used to programmatically initiate item editing.
        Normally, item editing is started by the user by slowly double-clicking
        an item. This method provides an alternative to this user mechanism.

        This will only work if @{"Listviewcolumn.Editable" LINK ListviewcolumnEditable} has been set to TRUE for
        the respective listview column.

        When the user has finished editing, the @{"Listview.ValueChange" LINK ListviewValueChange} attribute
        will be triggered.

        Note that if you have installed a listener on the @{"Listview.StartEditing" LINK ListviewStartEditing}
        attribute, then this callback will be asked for permission first before
        editing is actually started.

        To learn about editing operations getting cancelled, you can listen to
        the @{"Listview.AbortEditing" LINK ListviewAbortEditing} attribute.

        Also note that on AmigaOS and compatibles this feature is only available
        on MUI 4.0 or higher.

   @{b}INPUTS@{ub}
        id        id of the listview object
        row       row index of the item to edit
        column    column index of the item to edit

@ENDNODE

